===============================================================================
                            MINIMAL VIM & ZSH SETUP
===============================================================================

FOL download zsh with curl

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install vim-plug for Vim
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
curl -fLo ~/.vim/autoload/plug.vim --create-dirs \
     https://raw.githubusercontent.com/junegunn/vim-plug/master/plug.vim

In Vim mode:
  :PlugInstall

Reload Vim and enjoy a minimal setup without a heavy IDE.

This setup assumes some comfort using the keyboard for most tasks.
Perfect for old Linux or Darwin systems or for projects with huge
codebases (~1M lines) without relying on heavy IDEs like CLion.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Load Oh My Zsh
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
sh -c "$(curl -fsSL \
      https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh/master/tools/install.sh)"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Load a theme for Oh My Zsh
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ln -s $PWD/sobole.zsh-theme ~/.oh-my-zsh/custom/themes/sobole.zsh-theme

================================================================================
